obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47152)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979&sectionId=47152&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[1. Short title and extent.--(1) This Act may be called the Fatal Accidents Act, 1855.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951 s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (47153)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title `Suit for compensation to the family of a person for loss occasioned to it by his death by actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979&sectionId=47153&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A.] Suit for compensation to the family of a person for loss occasioned to it by his death by`
  line `actionable wrong.--Whenever the death of a person shall be caused by wrongful act, neglect or`
  line `default, and the act, neglect or default is such as would (if death had not ensured) have entitled the`
  line `party injured to maintain an action and recover damages in respect thereof, the party who would have`
  line `been liable if death had not ensued shall be liable to an action or suit for damages, notwithstanding the`
  line `death of the person injured, and although the death shall have been caused under such circumstances as`
  line `amount in law to felony or other crime.`
  line
  line `^2** * Every such action or suit shall be for the benefit of the wife, husband, parent and child, if any,`
  line `of the person whose death shall have been so caused, and shall be brought by and in the name of the`
  line `executor, administrator or representative of the person deceased;`
  line
  line `and in every such action the Court may give such damages as it may think proportioned to`
  line `the loss resulting from such death to the parties respectively, for whom and for whose benefit`
  line `such action shall be brought; and the amount so recovered, after deducting all costs and`
  line `expenses, including the costs not recovered from the defendant, shall be divided amongst the`
  line `before-mentioned parties, or any of them, a such shares as the Court by its judgment or decree`
  line `shall direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Original s. 1 re-numbered as s. lA by s. 3 and Sch., ibid.`
  line `2. The words "And it is enacted further that" omitted by Act 10 of 1914, Sch. II/`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47154)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title `Not more than one suit to be brought.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. The words "and that every such action shall be brought within twelve calendar months after the death of such deceased person" rep. by Act 9 of 1871, s. 2 and the First Schedule, see now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979&sectionId=47154&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Provided always that not more than one action or suit`
  line `shall be brought for, and in respect of the same subject-matter of complaint ^1`
  line `***:`
  line
  line `Claim for loss to estate may be added.--Provided that, in any such action or suit, the executor, administrator or representative of the deceased may insert a claim for and recover any pecuniary loss to the estate of the deceased occasioned by such wrongful act, neglect or default, which sum, when recovered, shall be deemed part of the assets of the estate of the deceased.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47155)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Plaintiff shall deliver particulars, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979&sectionId=47155&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The plaint in any such action or suit shall give a`
  line `full particular of the person or persons for whom, or on whose behalf, such action or suit shall be`
  line `brought, and of the nature of the claim in respect of which damages shall be sought to be`
  line recovered.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47156)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979&sectionId=47156&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00031_185513_1523265540979
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The following words and expressions are intended to have the meanings`
  line `hereby assigned to them respectively, so far as such meanings are not excluded by the context or by the nature of the subject-matter; that is to say ^1*** the word "person", shall apply to bodies politic and`
  line `corporate; and the word "parent" shall include father and mother^2`
  line `and grand-father and grand-mother;`
  line `and the word "child" shall include son and daughter and grand-son and grand-daughter and step-son and`
  line step-daughter.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Certain words omitted by Act 10 of 1914, Sch.`
  line
  line `2. Stepfather and step-mother are designedly omitted.`
